{"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/Host-Article","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The host application is the application that is currently using your keyboard. Being able to identify the host application is crucial if you want to adjust your keyboard for specific apps, and to make it possible for the main app to return to the keyboard."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Unfortunately, Apple are constantly making it harder for keyboard extensions to identify their host application, and for keyboards and apps to navigate to certain apps. And with iOS 26.4, things are worse than ever.","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"👑 KeyboardKit Pro unlocks additional ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardHostApplication","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" tools for licenses that include the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/ProFeature\/hostApplication","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" feature, to integrate with certain apps. You can sign up for KeyboardKit Pro from the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/keyboardkit.com","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","style":"important"},{"text":"Breaking changes in iOS 26.4","anchor":"Breaking-changes-in-iOS-264","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In iOS 26.4, Apple removed a private API that was used to resolve "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardInputViewController\/hostApplicationBundleId","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" from the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardInputViewController","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". Due to this, the host application feature has been adjusted to work around this severe limitation."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Since the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardInputViewController"},{"text":" can no longer resolve this ID, the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardContext"},{"type":"text","text":" has new ways to manage this."}]},{"text":"Host Application Bundle Identifier","anchor":"Host-Application-Bundle-Identifier","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardInputViewController"},{"type":"text","text":" can’t resolve a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardInputViewController\/hostApplicationBundleId"},{"type":"text","text":" anymore, the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardContext"},{"type":"text","text":" lets you set its "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardContext\/hostApplicationBundleId"},{"type":"text","text":" with code, or with a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardHostApplication"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardHostApplication\/Picker"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your keyboard must really know which host application that is using it, you should design your keyboard to let users pick the current application from a list. You can use the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardHostApplication\/allCases","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", or let users switch between certain apps."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Once the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardContext\/hostApplicationBundleId","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is set, you can use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardHostApplicationProvider\/hostApplication","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardHostApplicationProvider\/hostApplication(withAdditionalApps:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" to resolve a certain ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardHostApplication","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Opening the main app and returning to the keyboard","anchor":"Opening-the-main-app-and-returning-to-the-keyboard","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/Navigation-Article","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" article describes the details involved with opening the main application to perform a task, then return to the keyboard."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Tip","style":"tip","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Since Apple restricts keyboards from knowing about their host app, and restricts the main app from returning to the keyboard, you can use the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardAppContext\/openReason","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" to determine if you should present a message to show the user how to tap the top leading back button to return to the keyboard. For instance, opening the main app from the keyboard to start the dictation engine will set the reason to ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardApp\/OpenReason\/dictation","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".  The reason will auto-reset when the main app is sent to the background.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If letting the user select the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardContext\/hostApplicationBundleId","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" before opening the main app, you can use the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardHostApplicationProvider\/hostApplication","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" to navigate back to that app once you’re done in the main app, but this is only supported by a small subset of apps."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"%F0%9F%91%91-KeyboardKit-Pro","text":"👑 KeyboardKit Pro","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit Pro unlocks ways to identify specific apps, using a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardHostApplication","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type that defines many popular apps."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Host-Application","text":"Host Application","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"KeyboardKit Pro adds a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardHostApplicationProvider\/hostApplication","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" property to the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardContext","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":", which maps the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardInputViewController\/hostApplicationBundleId","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" to any of the following known applications:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"App Store, Apple Calendar, Apple Clock, Apple FaceTime, Apple Files, Apple Find My, Apple Health, Apple Maps, Apple Messages, Apple Music, Apple Music Classical, Apple News, Apple Notes, Apple Numbers, Apple Pages, Apple Photos, Apple Podcasts, Apple Reminders, Apple Settings, Apple Shortcuts, Apple Translate, Apple TV, Apple Weather, Amazon Prime, Bambu Handy, Bloomberg, Blue Sky, Brave, Bolt, ChatGPT, CityMapper, Discord, Disney+, Dropbox, DuckDuckGo, Duolingo, Facebook, Gmail, Goodnotes, Google Assistant, Google Calendar, Google Chat, Google Chrome, Google Docs, Google Drive, Google Home, Google Maps, Instagram, Ivory, KeyboardKit Demo, LinkedIn, Meetup, Messenger, Microsoft OneDrive, Netflix, 1Password, Signal, Slack, Snapchat, Spotify, Telegram, Trello, Twitch, X (Twitter), WhatsApp, Uber, YouTube","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can open any "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardHostApplication"},{"type":"text","text":" with "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardHostApplication\/open(withAction:)"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardHostApplication\/open(withActionHandler:)"},{"type":"text","text":" and access additional information about the app from the app value."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Adding-more-host-applications","text":"Adding more host applications","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardHostApplicationProvider\/hostApplication(withAdditionalApps:)"},{"text":" to match the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardHostApplicationProvider\/hostApplicationBundleId"},{"text":" with additional apps, if ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardHostApplication"},{"text":" doesn’t define certain apps that you need.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"info@keyboardkit.com","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" if you want to add more "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardHostApplication","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"s. We need the name of the app, and a deep link that can be used to open the app."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardHostApplication","doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardHostApplicationProvider"],"anchor":"Types","title":"Types"}],"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit